WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:46.040 --> 00:48.746
<i>Seasoned crooks swear you
only remember two days</i>

00:48.800 --> 00:50.982
<i>about your stretch in jail:</i>

00:51.040 --> 00:52.551
<i>The day you get in...</i>

00:55.040 --> 00:56.869
- Oh, boy.
<i>- ...and the day you get out.</i>

01:00.640 --> 01:04.346
<i>But I'll tell you, those guys,
they never been to a Polish prison.</i>

01:04.400 --> 01:06.741
<i>'Cause, buddy, you don't
forget a second of your stay</i>

01:06.800 --> 01:09.221
<i>in the Warsaw penal system.</i>

01:14.440 --> 01:16.622
Oh, boy.

01:16.720 --> 01:19.949
<i>And you never stop thinking about
what you done that got you there,</i>

01:20.000 --> 01:22.341
<i>and what you're going
to do when you get out.</i>

01:22.400 --> 01:25.902
<i>And who you're going to do it to.</i>

01:30.080 --> 01:32.581
<i>I reckon it takes a
betrayal before you realize</i>

01:32.640 --> 01:37.780
<i>the real currency in the world
ain't money... it's trust.</i>

01:40.040 --> 01:43.587
Hey. So, guess I'm topsies, huh?

01:45.880 --> 01:50.190
<i>'Cause if you got no trust...</i>

01:50.240 --> 01:52.820
Oh, boy.

01:52.920 --> 01:55.626
<i>Then what do you got?</i>

02:07.680 --> 02:11.546
<i>Now, there's no such thing
as one last big job,</i>

02:11.600 --> 02:13.748
<i>but Poland was pretty close.</i>

02:15.120 --> 02:19.111
<i>We were doing a smooth switch using
a standard base to our scam.</i>

02:19.200 --> 02:21.189
<i>The first thing you need is a mark.</i>

02:21.280 --> 02:24.224
<i>Stash Bartkowiak was just
like all the others:</i>

02:24.280 --> 02:28.430
<i>rich, corrupt and most
definitely dangerous.</i>

02:28.480 --> 02:31.663
<i>So Stash picks up a stolen Gauguin
ripped from an Oslo gallery</i>

02:31.720 --> 02:33.549
<i>by a couple of smash-and-grabbers.</i>

02:33.600 --> 02:35.429
<i>So, of course, he wants to get
the painting authenticated.</i>

02:35.480 --> 02:41.064
<i>But what he didn't know, was the man
he turned to was Nicky Calhoun.</i>

02:41.120 --> 02:43.826
<i>And Nicky Calhoun
is my half-brother.</i>

02:43.880 --> 02:47.541
<i>A crew needs an idea man
and ours was Nicky.</i>

02:47.640 --> 02:50.630
<i>Paddy McCarthy, he was our Rolodex,</i>

02:50.680 --> 02:52.862
<i>the guy who knows any
guy you need to know.</i>

02:52.920 --> 02:55.751
<i>And Guy De Cornet was our forger.</i>

02:55.800 --> 02:57.948
<i>Best scratcher I've ever known.</i>

02:58.000 --> 03:01.024
<i>Now there was a time,
if you ask anyone in our game,</i>

03:01.080 --> 03:03.990
<i>who the best damn
wheelman around was,</i>

03:04.040 --> 03:07.349
<i>and I'm guaranteeing you, you're going
to hear the name Crunch Calhoun.</i>

03:07.400 --> 03:10.470
<i>And that's got nothing to
do with how fast I drive</i>

03:10.520 --> 03:12.702
<i>and everything to do with trust.</i>

03:12.760 --> 03:15.431
<i>'Cause without that
you've got anarchy.</i>

03:15.480 --> 03:17.150
I like that jacket.

03:17.200 --> 03:18.980
Well, clothes tell you
a lot about the man.

03:19.000 --> 03:20.511
That's why it's a saying.

03:20.560 --> 03:22.310
I don't know, Nicky.
Take Guy there.

03:22.360 --> 03:25.589
The only thing his fancy white
leotard tells me is that

03:25.680 --> 03:27.464
he ain't circumcised.

03:27.560 --> 03:30.106
You misunderstand fashion.
Fatsoes. Look at you.

03:30.160 --> 03:31.910
- Fatsoes?
- Women go crazy for this...

03:31.960 --> 03:33.789
Boys! There it is!

03:36.480 --> 03:38.662
I'll see you at the lab, Crunch.

03:48.680 --> 03:51.306
Don't touch the art, lad.
All alarmed.

04:08.320 --> 04:11.469
Wow! Love the track suits.

04:11.560 --> 04:14.664
Fellas, I'd like you to
meet Professor O'Connor.

04:14.720 --> 04:16.947
Doc, these are the fellas.

04:17.000 --> 04:20.422
As I said, Dr. "O" here,
is real discreet.

04:20.480 --> 04:22.344
Very discreet, gentlemen.

04:24.680 --> 04:29.820
Oh. Paul Gauguin.
"Tahitian Beach," 1893.

04:29.880 --> 04:32.267
Painting is stolen. But is real?

04:32.320 --> 04:35.902
We'll see. Needs a density scan.

04:36.000 --> 04:37.704
What is density scan?

04:37.760 --> 04:40.989
I'm not so sure myself,
but doctor knows best.

04:58.240 --> 05:03.631
OK, great. So a guy walks
into a bar with a monkey.

05:18.280 --> 05:21.907
Oh. What is this?

05:21.960 --> 05:23.949
What?

05:24.000 --> 05:26.341
- No, no, no, no, no.
- What?

05:26.400 --> 05:28.389
- More red. More red.
- No, no, no, no, no.

05:28.440 --> 05:29.951
Don't do this, Guy, please.
You're killing me.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.023
They're identical.
Just swap the frames!

05:32.080 --> 05:33.705
My work...

05:33.760 --> 05:35.783
Oh fuck, Guy! Come on,
they're identical!

05:35.840 --> 05:38.705
- Just change them!
- My work must be perfect-o!

05:40.800 --> 05:42.311
You've got five minutes.

05:43.680 --> 05:45.942
So I say, "I'm looking for Mario."

05:46.000 --> 05:49.104
And this kid says, "There's
a thousand Marios in Naples."

05:49.200 --> 05:52.065
I say, "Yeah, but this
one's a criminal."

05:52.160 --> 05:57.061
And he goes, "Two thousand!"

05:58.080 --> 05:59.864
Guy. Guy.

05:59.960 --> 06:02.586
Guy! They will fucking
kill Nicky and Paddy

06:02.640 --> 06:05.061
if I don't make it
back there in time!

06:05.120 --> 06:09.623
Guy, you got ten seconds.
That's it. Ten!

06:09.720 --> 06:15.463
Nine, eight, seven,
six, five. Put it in.

06:15.560 --> 06:20.143
- Three, two, one. Now!
<i>- Au revoir.</i>

06:20.200 --> 06:22.701
You fuck!

06:32.840 --> 06:33.987
Bastard!

06:38.360 --> 06:41.509
So naturally I tell the Turkish
prostitute, "I'll take two."

07:11.440 --> 07:15.465
So are any of you guys Ukrainian?

07:15.520 --> 07:17.622
No? OK then.

07:29.360 --> 07:31.144
Ah, fuck!

08:05.120 --> 08:09.987
She's a genuine Gauguin,
boys. Priceless.

08:15.800 --> 08:17.902
I don't believe this.

08:17.960 --> 08:20.711
There's millions of dollars of
paintings and we're doing nothing.

08:20.760 --> 08:23.067
- Leave it, lad.
- This is Poland!

08:23.120 --> 08:25.268
We can do whatever
the fuck we want.

08:25.320 --> 08:27.184
Nicky, boy,
the Gauguin's worth more

08:27.240 --> 08:30.071
than five rooms of paintings in
this place and they're all alarmed.

08:30.120 --> 08:33.144
Are you kidding me?
There's no alarms.

08:36.480 --> 08:37.581
There's alarms.

09:03.880 --> 09:05.630
Boys, let's all split up!

09:05.680 --> 09:10.024
Train to Berlin. Ten AM.
Bright and early like!

09:11.320 --> 09:13.149
Shit!

09:24.720 --> 09:29.860
Go! Here. What are you...
what are you...?! Wrong way!

09:32.640 --> 09:35.186
<i>That crash was a stroke of luck.</i>

09:36.360 --> 09:39.145
<i>And the cops showed up
before Stash could kill him.</i>

09:40.880 --> 09:42.470
Uh...

09:42.560 --> 09:45.823
Did I tell you the
one about the, uh,

09:45.880 --> 09:48.347
three prostitutes and
the bruised melon?

09:51.280 --> 09:53.109
We only want painting back.

09:53.160 --> 09:55.945
One painting, one arrest.

09:56.000 --> 09:58.546
It could be you or someone else.

10:00.680 --> 10:06.469
You have record in Europe,
so that's 20 years sentence.

10:07.640 --> 10:09.265
We make deal, huh?

10:09.320 --> 10:12.947
The painting and a fall guy.

10:14.720 --> 10:18.222
<i>For Nicky, I figure it
was just basic math.</i>

10:18.280 --> 10:20.951
<i>He's facing 20 years and
I got a clean sheet.</i>

10:21.000 --> 10:24.946
<i>I can't blame him for that.
But I can hate him for it.</i>

10:27.640 --> 10:29.469
Oh, boy.

10:48.000 --> 10:50.262
<i>So I went home.</i>

10:50.320 --> 10:53.549
<i>And I couldn't go back to the life.</i>

10:53.600 --> 10:56.101
<i>The trust was gone.</i>

10:56.160 --> 10:58.149
<i>Crew was gone.</i>

10:58.200 --> 11:00.701
<i>And everybody went
their separate ways.</i>

11:02.200 --> 11:05.747
<i>And I met a girl.
Someone I could bank on.</i>

11:05.800 --> 11:07.743
<i>And even if I couldn't,
buddy, I'll tell you,</i>

11:07.800 --> 11:10.790
<i>she wasn't the worst person
I shared a bunk with lately.</i>

11:10.840 --> 11:13.705
<i>But I could bank on Francie.</i>

11:13.760 --> 11:17.785
<i>Francie was a young buck I caught
pinching hubcaps off my truck.</i>

11:17.840 --> 11:20.671
<i>Most folks probably would have called
the cops, but I gave him a job.</i>

11:20.720 --> 11:25.621
<i>'Cause every new and then,
you got to take a leap of faith.</i>

11:25.680 --> 11:29.626
Hey, Crunch. Lace 'em up.

11:32.240 --> 11:35.981
The only way we're gonna get the crowd
tomorrow is if you take a dive today.

11:36.040 --> 11:38.746
Nope, not gonna happen, not again.

11:38.840 --> 11:41.989
It pains me to say it, Crunch, but the
only reason why these folks are here

11:42.040 --> 11:43.949
is in the hope that you
crack your skull open.

11:44.000 --> 11:47.104
You have to crash your bike.
That's what you do.

11:47.160 --> 11:50.309
<i>One hundred eighty-eight
stitches, 26 broken bones.</i>

11:50.360 --> 11:54.101
<i>Twelve totaled bikes. Three comes.</i>

11:54.160 --> 11:56.308
<i>Twice pronounced legally dead.</i>

11:56.400 --> 12:01.984
<i>- I'll give you $700.
- The one, the only, Crunch Calhoun!</i>

12:03.600 --> 12:07.102
Let me say this out loud,
'cause I can't believe my own ears.

12:07.200 --> 12:12.750
You expect me to deliberately take a
dive, risk my life, for 700 bucks?

12:14.280 --> 12:16.621
- Twelve.
- Seven.

12:16.680 --> 12:18.305
- Eleven.
- Six.

12:18.360 --> 12:20.349
- Eight.
- Deal.

12:20.400 --> 12:21.786
Call the ambulance.

12:28.640 --> 12:30.310
Ladies and gentlemen,

12:30.360 --> 12:32.064
let's give old Crunch
a moment of silence

12:32.120 --> 12:36.862
as he prepares to go down, down,
down into the ring of fire!

12:36.920 --> 12:38.660
How'd she do? Tell me
at least a thousand.

12:38.680 --> 12:42.023
No, $800. So just
don't do it, Crunch.

12:42.080 --> 12:44.148
I'll pay you $800 not to spill 'er.

12:44.240 --> 12:46.547
If you got $800,
I'm payin' you too much.

12:46.600 --> 12:49.988
Just don't do it, bud.

12:50.080 --> 12:54.708
I'll be all right, Francie. Besides,
"Fortune favors the bold."

12:54.760 --> 12:56.464
Who said that one?

12:56.520 --> 12:58.861
- Virgil.
- Right.

14:03.800 --> 14:07.063
Excuse me, sir. Would you
consent to a voluntary search?

14:12.000 --> 14:15.661
- Right this way, please.
- Bad luck, chief.

14:18.480 --> 14:19.911
Thank you.

14:24.240 --> 14:25.865
Ground rules, same as last time.

14:25.920 --> 14:29.229
You talk when I tell you to talk
and when I don't, you do not talk.

14:29.280 --> 14:31.348
Don't bark at me. I'm not your dog.

14:31.400 --> 14:35.346
Did I say to talk? Because I don't
recall telling you to talk.

14:35.400 --> 14:37.343
How many more times
must I do your job

14:37.400 --> 14:40.026
before I've paid my
proverbial debt to society?

14:40.080 --> 14:43.946
Warning: You make me look
stupid, I will crush you.

14:45.600 --> 14:48.101
- That looked hot.
- Yes, a little bit.

14:48.160 --> 14:49.910
We're going to start with
"good cop, bad cop".

14:49.960 --> 14:51.505
- I'm not a cop.
- OK.

14:51.560 --> 14:53.583
How about "good cop,
just do what I fuckin' say"?

14:53.640 --> 14:55.265
You're not a cop.

14:55.320 --> 14:59.106
Correction. The "pol" in
Interpol, it stands for police.

14:59.160 --> 15:02.150
- Then where is your pistol?
- I don't need a gun.

15:02.200 --> 15:04.189
I've got something far
more dangerous than that.

15:04.240 --> 15:07.105
Is it a whistle that you blow
to summon the real police

15:07.160 --> 15:11.231
- when a crime is being committed?
- No. It's actually a pen.

15:11.280 --> 15:14.463
And, with it, I can
deny your parole.

15:14.520 --> 15:17.385
So why don't you shut the
hell up and follow my lead?

15:19.120 --> 15:21.188
Where's the fucking
painting, fucko?

15:22.600 --> 15:25.226
Whoa.

15:25.320 --> 15:28.788
My name is Agent Bick. This is
my associate, Samuel Winter.

15:29.960 --> 15:31.585
I know Sam.

15:31.640 --> 15:33.344
Sam, what are you doing
with Dirty Harry, here?

15:33.400 --> 15:35.741
You know how they pair
professional athletes

15:35.800 --> 15:37.470
- with slow kids?
- Yep.

15:37.520 --> 15:39.145
It's kind of like that.

15:40.520 --> 15:43.669
Two weeks ago, this
painting "Model, Rear-View"

15:43.720 --> 15:47.029
by Georges Seurat was stolen by
an art collector in Mexico City

15:47.080 --> 15:48.705
by a woman we had
under surveillance.

15:48.800 --> 15:51.870
Yeah, I've never seen
that woman before...

15:51.920 --> 15:53.306
before yesterday.

15:53.360 --> 15:55.701
Do I look like a
fucking clown to you?

15:55.760 --> 15:59.069
Clowns try to be funny. You're
just unintentionally hysterical.

15:59.120 --> 16:01.188
Shut your giggle hole

16:01.240 --> 16:03.422
and open the damn case.

16:05.240 --> 16:07.741
It's called "Tio Puno Loco".

16:07.800 --> 16:10.426
Which translates
"Uncle Crazy Fist."

16:10.480 --> 16:13.550
Now, if you gentlemen will excuse
me, I've got to water ski...

16:13.600 --> 16:16.909
Sit down! Winter,
this is not "pointerism".

16:16.960 --> 16:19.381
Every painting tells a story.

16:20.520 --> 16:24.306
- All good art tells a story.
- This one tells two.

16:25.720 --> 16:28.391
<i>Say Nicky here is
stopped at Customs.</i>

16:28.440 --> 16:32.590
<i>All they see is this rubbish,</i>

16:32.640 --> 16:35.505
<i>not the masterpiece underneath.</i>

16:35.560 --> 16:39.346
<i>Acetate solution loosens
the top acrylic layer.</i>

16:39.400 --> 16:45.109
<i>Peel it on back and you're left with
the original oil painting underneath.</i>

16:45.160 --> 16:48.070
What the fuck is that?

16:48.120 --> 16:52.862
It's a marvelous picture. I'm delighted
to have it as part of my collection.

16:52.920 --> 16:57.230
Well, boys, have a nice day.

16:58.560 --> 17:00.344
Where's the Seurat?!

17:00.400 --> 17:03.424
Long gone.

17:08.160 --> 17:09.989
- Sunny.
- Yeah. How'd it go?

17:10.040 --> 17:11.550
Ah, it went.

17:11.599 --> 17:13.987
Bad luck, chief.

17:17.160 --> 17:18.829
You got the money?

17:20.240 --> 17:21.340
There you go.

17:23.440 --> 17:25.986
- It feels a little light.
- Well, why don't you open it?

17:27.760 --> 17:29.146
"I'm sorry.

17:30.480 --> 17:31.820
I'm sorry for hitting
you with a lead pipe."

17:31.880 --> 17:33.823
What the fuck...

17:46.120 --> 17:48.302
Crunch, honey, we're out of ice.

17:48.360 --> 17:50.747
Oh yeah, all right.

17:53.240 --> 17:55.741
- Thank you, Crunchie.
- Adios, fellas.

17:55.840 --> 17:59.626
Ice? $50 for ice? It's wintertime.

17:59.720 --> 18:01.709
Crunch, she's, she's not
even trying anymore.

18:01.760 --> 18:05.342
- Happy wife, happy life, right?
- So you say.

18:05.400 --> 18:07.980
Oh, I don't know, Francie.

18:08.040 --> 18:11.747
When I was a young buck
I thought I'd make history,

18:11.800 --> 18:15.109
not just sit there
reading about it.

18:17.520 --> 18:20.191
Hell, I thought I'd be a great man.

18:20.280 --> 18:26.342
OK, so you're not... stereotypically
great, like Alexander the Great.

18:26.400 --> 18:31.347
But you're great like,
great like, like...

18:31.400 --> 18:33.025
You're a great guy!

18:33.080 --> 18:36.468
Great men don't take dives for
a couple of hundred bucks.

18:38.000 --> 18:41.627
And great men don't
miss their fate.

18:41.720 --> 18:45.188
Somewhere along the line I...

18:45.240 --> 18:48.184
I missed mine, Francie.

18:48.240 --> 18:51.184
I was probably staring at it
the whole time and I just...

18:52.800 --> 18:54.584
I missed it.

18:57.000 --> 19:01.424
My God, you're a downer.
A fuckin' boner killer.

19:01.480 --> 19:02.547
And what are you going to do?

19:02.600 --> 19:04.639
Are you gonna sell fuckin'
insurance or something?

19:04.640 --> 19:07.903
Just shut the fuck up
and cheer up, please.

19:08.000 --> 19:11.661
Allow me.

19:13.400 --> 19:16.822
- Yo, Dennis Calhoun?
- Who's asking?

19:17.880 --> 19:20.551
- It's fuckin' Sunny.
- Sounds about right.

19:20.600 --> 19:25.388
Hey, Crunch, there's some guy with
an eye-patch here to see you.

19:41.200 --> 19:43.587
Oh, easy, man!

19:43.640 --> 19:46.027
Where's your fuckin' brother?

19:46.120 --> 19:49.160
I was gonna cut bait and go home then
I realized Nicky said he had a brother.

19:52.400 --> 19:54.980
Oww. Fuck!

19:56.760 --> 20:01.422
Sweet Baby Jesus.
What are you, a pirate?

20:03.080 --> 20:05.479
Hey, hey, hey. Look! I don't
know where Nicky is, all right.

20:05.480 --> 20:07.662
- He said you work with him.
- Yeah, a long time ago.

20:07.720 --> 20:10.346
Now, look, I got like $300
stashed in the bedroom there.

20:10.400 --> 20:13.231
It's yours. A guy in your line of
work might prefer doubloons...

20:13.280 --> 20:14.381
I'm not a fuckin' pirate!

20:17.000 --> 20:18.829
I don't even talk to Nicky.
I hate him.

20:18.880 --> 20:21.426
Here's what's what.
I want the 30 grand

20:21.480 --> 20:23.582
- or I want that fuckin' painting.
- What painting?

20:23.640 --> 20:26.391
- The Seurat.
- Whoa! Whoa! What?

20:26.440 --> 20:27.826
- The Seurat!
- What?

20:27.880 --> 20:30.551
The Georges Seurat,
you ignorant fuck!

20:30.600 --> 20:32.702
The seminal French
"Post-Impressionalist".

20:32.760 --> 20:36.831
The father of pointillism. That
Georges Seurat, you fuckin' baboon.

20:36.920 --> 20:40.627
Now I want the
30 grand, the painting

20:40.680 --> 20:42.908
or a bullet in your fucking head!

20:46.400 --> 20:48.309
Hey, uh...

20:48.360 --> 20:51.191
- Crunch, is everything OK?
- Yeah.

20:51.240 --> 20:53.946
What... what's happening, exactly?

20:54.000 --> 20:57.388
- Nothing.
- What?

20:57.480 --> 20:59.787
I'm being held at
gunpoint by a pirate.

20:59.840 --> 21:01.465
I'm in the bathroom.
What do you think, Francie?

21:01.520 --> 21:04.305
All right. Sorry for
fuckin' askin'!

21:04.360 --> 21:06.986
I ain't leavin'
without the 30 grand.

21:07.040 --> 21:11.828
Sorry, Sinbad, but I don't think
that musketoon's gonna even fire.

21:11.880 --> 21:15.348
So go ahead and pull the trigger
'cause I got no painting,

21:15.400 --> 21:19.186
no Nicky and no 30 fucking grand!

21:23.960 --> 21:25.630
Who owns that fuckin' bike outside?

21:25.720 --> 21:27.185
Wait a minute, man.

21:36.320 --> 21:40.391
- What the fuck?
- What's going on?

21:40.480 --> 21:43.390
- Nicky's back.
- What?

21:43.440 --> 21:44.905
And so am I.

21:44.960 --> 21:48.143
What the fuck just happened?

21:48.240 --> 21:52.311
Fate! Fate is what just happened.

21:52.520 --> 21:54.145
<i>Uncle Paddy.</i>

21:54.200 --> 21:56.587
How are you, lad?
Still in the land of the living?

21:56.640 --> 21:59.505
You wanted to know when I was
ready to go back to work.

21:59.560 --> 22:01.424
Well, I'm ready.

22:05.960 --> 22:07.710
- Citizenship?
- Various.

22:07.800 --> 22:09.186
Anything to declare?

22:09.240 --> 22:12.549
Nothing but my undying
